
// Replaces all occurrences of the carriage return character "\r" in the content of the first choice message from an HTTP POST response with an empty string, effectively removing them. The [strings.replace] slot targets the specific content node within the HTTP response structure using a lambda expression.
strings.replace:x:@http.post/*/content/*/choices/0/*/message/*/content
   .:"\r"
   .:
